1:
- Start button -> backend request -> new game -> game.start()
  - (2x) new player
    - (6x) new card (2 of each type)

2:
- Grid button -> backend request -> game.board.actions(square)
  - returns actions that can be taken from grid (attack, move, build)
  - said action buttons are then enabled 

-- KEY: attack, move, and build buttons are disabled by default, only enabled when a grid is selected

3:
- Attack button -> backend request -> game.return valid attack targets

To attack:
-> Select friendly grid -> attack button is enabled -> click attack button -> possible target grids are lit up -> select target grid

4: Target grid selected -> backend request -> attack happens

-- To play a card -> click the card, then click a tile to play it on -- this info is then sent to backend